Company Description
For more than 100 years STADA is taking care of a great good: your health. The care of health and well-being of people is the center of STADA's trade. The company's Philosophy and mission statement is based on it.


Job requirements
- Bookkeeping activities up to final Trial Balance (AP, AR, Petty Cash, Bank, Fixed Assets, Deferred Expenses, Expenses in Advance, Leasing – split on cost centers/cost elements);
- Knowledge of RAS and local tax legislation;
- Preparation of Balance Sheet and P&L statements;
- Profit tax calculation;
- Timely and correct preparation of monthly tax returns statements;
- Taxes on property;
- Liaise with local authorities;
- Monthly preparation of IFRS Group Reporting package;
- Disclosures of all Balance Sheet items;
- Disclosures of IC expenses/income, monthly IC reconciliations;
- Monthly preparation of Cash Flow Report;
- Monitoring of the 3rd party agreements, related invoices and payments;
- Manual calculation of cost of goods sold in case of improper software work;
- Prepare the annual inventory;

Working experience 
- Minimum 5 years’ experience in accounting, out of which at least 3 years in similar position;

Qualifications and skills
- University degree in Economics;
- Knowledge of English language – business level, as a must;
- Advanced Excel for manipulation of huge volume of information at short notice;
- Good communication and interpersonal skills;
- Proactive, organized, exact and efficient working style;
- Advantage is knowledge of WizCount software;

We are offering
- The opportunity to work in an international environment;  
- Competitive salary package;  
- A place to grow professionally and be rewarded for your loyalty;  
- A nice environment in a fast-growing company;
